    "name": "Julien Kasper",
    "profile": "Julien Kasper's keen interest in music was sparked at the age of eight when -- like so many musicians -- he heard the Beatles for the first time. His subsequent obsession with music led to the purchase of his first guitar and by the age of 15, was soon jamming with the local funk band in his hometown Tallahassee, FL.\r\n\r\nNot long after he turned 16, Kasper started playing with harmonica ace/singer Pat Ramsey in the blues-rock band Crosscut Saw. The band developed a large fan base along the Eastern Seaboard and opened shows for artists such as B.B. King, Bobby Bland, and Bo Diddley.\r\n\r\nKasper later moved to Austin, TX, and was recruited to play in the original world music/fusion band Eloise Burrell & Trickle Down, touring regularly throughout Texas and New Mexico.\r\n\r\nTo further his musical development and to help him cultivate his growing passion for jazz, Kasper moved to Miami to attend the University of Miami's jazz and studio music program on a scholarship. He worked his way through s",
